All Anti-Hindutva Political Parties Should Be Banned, Says Togadia

Pune:  At the end of a three-day brainstorming session in Pune on Sunday, a=
 belligerent Vishwa Hindu Parishad (VHP) leadership slammed the secular par=
ties while coming out strongly in support of its stated policies of Hindu r=
ashtra and jehadi terrorists.

The VHP international secretary Praveen Togadia demanded the government to =
ban all secular and anti-Hindutva political parties, and held out a clear w=
arning to the minorities: Gujarat riots happened because of Godhra and if t=
he incident is repeated, riots will happen again.

Addressing a rally, dubbed a "dharma sabha", Togadia said, "There are three=
 Mohammad Ghaznis here. The first are the jehadi terrorists, the second are=
 the secularists and the third are the non-Hindu parties".

Holding the Godhra carnage directly responsible for the Gujarat riots, Toga=
dia said if such events happened again, incidents like Naroda Patiya would =
be repeated. Without naming the Congress, Togadia said, "If any party wishe=
s to rule India, it has to accept the concept of Hindu rashtra".

He said politics in India had to be based on Hinduism and called for all Hi=
ndus to be organised into an army to erase the existence of Pakistan and to=
 restore an "Akhand Bharat" (unified India).

Matching the hostile tenor, VHP president Ashok Singhal asked Muslims to gi=
ve up their claims to Kashi and Mathura. He said the VHP would build huge t=
emples in both the cities. Singhal said the VHP would pressurize the Centre=
 to hand over the disputed site in Ayodhya to the Ram Janmabhoomi Nyas, a t=
rust responsible for the building of Ram Temple. He said it (VHP) would, if=
 necessary, go for a showdown with the Centre on the issue of temple constr=
uction in Ayodhya and said it would fully abide by the decision of Hindu `s=
ants'.=20

His remarks came after the VHP asked the Centre to hand over the disputed t=
emple site in Ayodhya to the Ram Janambhoomi Trust before February-end.=20


